Black Walnut Praline Cake
  --@wickdconnfections

Cake:
2 c ap flour (250 g)
1 tsp baking powder (5 g)
1/2 tsp salt (3 g)
1 c unsalted butter, softened (226 g)
2 c  sugar (400 g)
4 large eggs
1 c buttermilk (240 ml)
1 tsp vanilla  (5 ml)
1 c chopped black walnuts (120 g)

Preheat oven to 350F / 175C. Grease and flour a 10-12 c Bundt or tube pan. In a bowl, whisk together flour, baking powder, and salt. Set aside. In a large bowl, cream butter and sugar until light and fluffy, ~3-4 min. Add eggs one at a time, mixing well after each addition. Mix in vanilla. Alternate adding the dry ingredients and buttermilk to the butter mixture, beginning and ending with dry ingredients. Mix until just combined. Fold in chopped black walnuts. Pour batter into prepared pan and smooth the top. Bake 30-40 min for layers or 50-60 min for Bundt or tube pan, until a toothpick inserted in the center comes out clean. Let cool in pan 10-15 min, then remove to a wire rack.

Glaze:
1/2 c unsalted butter (113 g)
1 c packed brown sugar (200 g)
1/4 c milk (60 ml)
1/2 c chopped black walnuts (60 g)

In a saucepan over medium heat, melt butter. Stir in brown sugar and milk. Bring to a gentle simmer and cook 2-3 min until slightly thickened. Remove from heat and stir in chopped black walnuts. Pour warm glaze over warm cake and allow it to set.
